title: The POWER To THRILL: CLX Results
body_text:
A predominant main event for the ages! The most fierce, in-your-face, gifted female entities to ever grace
EastCoastDodgeball's
hallowed battlegrounds head-to-head in one of the most eagerly-awaited clashes ever! "Giant Killer"
MELISSA KERR
, bad-ass
KERRIN MARCHESE
-
the "Dream Encounter" no one thought possible!
Not surprisingly, it got ugly and nasty real fast at the 160th spectacle as each of the respected army generals wanted to get it on. Captain Kerrin, backed by the unrelenting resources of heavy-hitter Dan Fitzpatrick, multi-time headliner Ryan Letsche, and the incomparable powerhouse and first overall choice Kevin Fitzpatrick, fired weapons left, right, and center at their helpless prey in both the opening contest and the next.
But "Killer" Kerr refused to go down without a fight as she, along with supporting players catching phenom Mike "Sputz" Krott, deadly southpaw Kevin Megill, and the self-proclaimed "Creation" and Kerr's first selection John Tronolone, would not be counted out just yet.
The evenly-fought confrontation would continue the same way it started. The next two contests were divided among the pair of furious females, setting the score at 3 to 2, in favor of Marchese.
Captain Kerr's golden chance to tie in the crucial sixth however ended up falling short and her no-nonsense, kick-ass adversary started to pull ahead. The rounds that followed would also belong to the Maryland native, running away with the match as the night progressed. After the conclusion of eight grueling contests, it was Captain Kerrin whose hand was raised in triumph.
Kerrin Marchese
defeated
Melissa Kerr
, 6 - 2, at the 160th EastCoastDodgeball extravaganza.
This nearly four-hour long war was as brutal and barbaric as it could possibly get. The cold October feel coupled with the explosive heat of the bulletballs produced several dozen casualties when this thing was all said and done.
The night's secondary attraction pitted 13 of the most recognized names of the modern era in one over-sized free-for-all! The quick and agile rookie-turned-legend
Bobby Vetrano
managed to escape defeat, lastly eliminating the iconic Chris Adams to capture the hard-fought victory.
Other combatants that took part in this season finale first were Dan Fitzpatrick, Ryan McCrorey, Michael Edwards, Travis Mills, Zach Katz, Sascha Basista, Jon Yochum, Mike "Sputz" Krott, former one-time winner Ryan Letsche, former four-time winner Kevin Fitzpatrick, former five-time winner John Tronolone, 2nd runner-up Michael Canzanella, and 1st runner-up Chris Adams.
Season 16
Two feud-ending
Pick Your Poison
confrontations, the memorable 3 Year Anniversary and Mid-Season Father/Son showdowns, and the birthday
CREAMation
were just a fraction of the incredible highlights over the last ten weeks.
The average attendance was a remarkable 29.0, with half of the events reaching turnouts of at least 30. Throughout the ten weeks,
ECD
welcomed 20 new stars.
There were two
Wet Wars
: DODGEBALL 154 (3 Year Anniversary) and John Tronolone's birthday event, DODGEBALL 157, which featured the
CREAMation
match-up between Alison Bertsch and Pam D'Luhy.
Diana DiBuccio, Kevin Megill, John Tronolone, Melissa Kerr, and Ryan Letsche participated in every Season 16 event, spanning from DODGEBALL 151 on August 16 to the season-ender DODGEBALL CLX.
DODGEBALL CLX
Decorations consisted mainly of dark blue, light blue, and white streamers draped along the fence and tennis nets. Like DODGEBALL CXL in May, three laminated CLX signs were also hung.
The soundtrack was a compiled list of songs from "The Writer". Soundgarden, Journey, Stone Temple Pilots, John Legend, Nine Inch Nails, Saliva, and Ya Kid K were just some of the artists featured in the 55-song playlist.
The special
Thanksgiving Food Drive
hosted by the Township of Ocean Human Services collected a terrific amount of canned and boxed goods, specifically from the Spengeman, Katz, and Adams families.
First pick for Captain Kerrin Marchese:
Kevin Fitzpatrick
First pick for Captain Melissa Kerr:
John Tronolone
Non-participating relatives on hand for DODGEBALL CLX were
Ms. Adams and Zoe Adams
(Mother and dog of Chris, Steve, and Tom Adams)
,
Mrs. Kerr
(Mother of Ryan and Melissa Kerr)
,
Jen Mullen
(Fiance of Ryan Kerr, future sister-in-law of Melissa Kerr)
,
Mr. and Mrs. Spengeman
(Father and mother of Dan Spengeman)
,
Mrs. Pontecorvo, Mr. Pontecorco, and Grandma Tronolone
(Aunt, uncle, and paternal grandmother of John and Michael Tronolone; Sister, brother-in-law, and mother of Mr. Darrell Tronolone; extended family members of Mr. Ed Walker and Nicholas Walker)
.
Online Exclusive!
Finding a suitable, deserving opponent for Melissa Kerr put "The Writer" in a tough position for several months. One of the original choices was Michael "Sputz" Krott, who declined entry into DODGEBALL CLX multiple times.
The other and final selection, Kerrin Marchese, graciously accepted the challenge midway through Season 16. Captain Kerrin took time off from work and drove nearly three hours from her home state of Maryland to attend.
Two "killer" captains, grapefruit-sized welts, and family members galore! Here are some of the unforgettable moments from
Power
CLX!
It's only fitting to begin with the leading ladies
Kerr
and
Kerrin
. Their outfits - tie-dyed T-Shirts, high black socks, athletic sneakers - set worry in the eyes of their enemies.
If your eyes missed some of the action, your ears sure as hell didn't! There were some physically-scarring bodyshots that fortunately did not require hospitalization. Both
Dan Spengeman
and
Kevin Fitzpatrick
were met with rocket bulletballs to the skull while
Dan Fitzpatrick
and newbie
Michael Canzanella
likely had their Adam's Apple knocked inward.
Ryan Letsche's
maniacal obsession with eliminating members of the
Tronolone
clan, the "underhand" tactics of "The Crazy One"
Michael Edwards
, and the laugh-out-loud foot/ankle bulletball snag by
"Muffin Man" Londono
sent players and warriors home with a mind full of pictures.
The jackpot
attendance of 39
is the 6th highest ever recorded, comprised of 31 men and 8 women. Other season finales with the same overall turnout are
DODGEBALL CX
in November 2007 and
DODGEBALL CXL:
Family Affair
in May 2008.
DODGEBALL CLX welcomed
three new players
, all of which related to members of the current roster:
Michael Canzanella
(Brother of Kimmy Canzanella)
,
Mr. Ed Walker
(Uncle of John and Michael Tronolone, Brother-in-law of Mr. Darrell Tronolone)
, and his son
Nicholas Walker
(Cousin of John and Michael Tronolone, Nephew of Mr. Darrell Tronolone)
.
Familiar Faces
returning after lengthy absences included the likes of Ben Cotta, Ryan Kerr, Kimmy Canzanella, Tom Adams, Michael Tronolone, Mr. Darrell Tronolone, and even the captain herself, Kerrin Marchese.
The official theme song was "Thriller" by Michael Jackson and the tagline was
The Power
as seen on one of the many promotional posters.
DODGEBALL CLX was the third consecutive season finale to be held on the back courts of Wall High School, the ninth overall. It was also the third finale held in the month of October, the first at 2005's
DODGEBALL X
and the second in 2006 at
DODGEBALL LX
. March, August, and October have played host to more ten events than any other months of the year.
In the night's secondary attraction,
Bobby Vetrano
won the massive 13-person Battle Royal. This was the first Battle Royal to ever take place at a ten event.
And in the colossal "dream bout" main event, Kerrin Marchese knocked off Melissa Kerr in a stunning 8 round match-up. This was the first female-only singles match-up in season finale history. The final score was 6 to 2.
Melissa Kerr
made her second season finale captains appearance, having headlined the Season 11 Finale, DODGEBALL CX, teaming with Michael "Sputz" Krott against Michael Butler and Alison Bertsch. This was Kerr's first-ever singles match. Her record is 0-2-0.
Kerrin Marchese
made her season finale captains debut. She had faced Diana DiBuccio in two separate singles match-ups in the Fall of 2006. Her record is 1-1-1.
Excluding DODGEBALL CLX's new players, the following competitors made their ten event debut: Jon Yochum, Jamie Biesiada, and Tom Auchinleck.
Electric Streamers and Signs!
Special thanks to both Sascha Basista and John Tronolone for putting up the streamers all around the court. The posters were co-created by Mike "Sputz" Krott and Captain Melissa Kerr, so they too are thanked for their decorations assistance.
Power Soundtrack!
Special thanks to "The Writer" for providing the music for the event as well as Dan Spengeman for allowing the use of his speakers.
Thanks For Giving!
Indeed a special thanks to the Adams, Spengeman, and Katz families for contributing towards Ocean Township's Annual Thanksgiving Food Drive.
I Love My Dodgeball!
Everyone who came, saw, and experienced the pageantry and the pain of DODGEBALL CLX are truly thanked for their continued efforts.
EastCoastDodgeball
sees no end in sight and it's because of people like you that make every attempt to attend.
Give EastCoastDodgeball your thoughts on DODGEBALL CLX: The Power !
